    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="161"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 626</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.062–<gloss target="#t_WFTU1"
                    >WFTU</gloss>/4–2451: Telegram.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria (<persName corresp="#p_DWC1"
                            type="from">Dowling</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d161fn1">Repeated to London, Paris for <gloss
                            target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>, and Brussels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-24T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 24, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2450. Notwithstanding info character of Dept <gloss target="#t_intel1"
                        >intel</gloss> Jan 30<note n="2" xml:id="d161fn2">Not printed, but see the
                        circular airgram, Document 607.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Leg1">Leg</gloss> at that time approached Aus Gov and <gloss
                        target="#t_TU1">TU</gloss> Fed re possibility <gloss target="#t_WFTU1"
                        >WFTU</gloss> establishing headquarters Vienna after expulsion Paris (<gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2208 [<hi rend="italic">2200</hi>] April
                        20<note n="3" xml:id="d161fn3">Document 624.</note>). Both promised to
                    observe and inform us any indications but pointed out little could be done under
                    occupation regime if Sovs chose to bring <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss>
                    here.</p>
                <p>On April 19 Communist Party official paper <hi rend="italic">Volksstimme</hi>
                    carried editorial announcing “at invitation Aust workers” and “to honor
                    Austrians” <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> would establish headquarters in
                    Coburg Palace. This building in first (international) district Vienna,
                    Seilerstaette 3, and is headquarters of Austro-Soviet Friendship Society and
                    Soviet-administered oil products distributors Orop.</p>
                <p>Aus Gov and <gloss target="#t_TU1">TU</gloss>’s caught unaware. At April 19
                    opening postal <gloss target="#t_TU1">TU</gloss> convention <gloss
                        target="#t_TU1">TU</gloss> Fed Pres Boehm denied invitation and offered as
                    first assignment for <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> defense of workers
                    striking against Sov administered Vamag metal working plant just outside Vienna.
                    Aus Gov also issued press statement that they were not consulted and no
                    permission requested. Socialist members of Aus Gov examining legal requirements
                    for possible bars in addition to making Sov sponsorship obvious. Aus <gloss
                        target="#t_TU1">TU</gloss> Fed not especially concerned and wishes avoid
                    publicity.</p>
                <pb facs="0285" n="1251" xml:id="pg_1251"/>
                <p>Dept may wish explore possibility of action by three west <gloss
                        target="#t_HICOM1">HICOM</gloss>s against such of their natls as come to
                    Vienna to serve with <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss>. In this regard, Dept
                    will note that Secretary <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss>, Louis Saillant,
                    is French natl.</p>
                <p>March letter to <gloss target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> regarding <gloss
                        target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> press and info Dept was form letter. Correct
                    address was Schwindgasse 7/6. Address is obviously blind since location is
                    apartment house with no tenant named Winter. Aus <gloss target="#t_TU1"
                        >TU</gloss>’s request above info on <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> be
                    passed to <gloss target="#t_ICFTU1">ICFTU</gloss> Brussels for all possible
                    action and Dept realizes that for some purposes Vienna is behind Iron
                    Curtain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dowling</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
